Botswana Finds Outbreak of Foot & Mouth in Northern Region, Ministry Says

-- B y   J e r r y   B u n g u
-- 
2011-05-06T07:45:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-06/botswana-finds-outbreak-of-foot-mouth-in-northern-region-ministry-says.html
Botswana  declared an outbreak of foot
and mouth disease in the northern part of the southern African
country near the border with  Zimbabwe , the Ministry of
Agriculture said in a statement.  The movement of animals and animal products has been
stopped and check points set up to ensure against transport to
other regions, the Gaborone-based ministry said in a statement
on its website today.  “Numerous cases of sick animals in about 300 cattle have
so far been reported showing feet and oral lesions normally
associated with the disease,” it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jerry Bungu in Gaborone at 
 jbungu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gordon Bell at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  